#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "Receiving compressed messages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid ""
"REST Client also supports receiving compressed messages using GZIP and can be enabled via configuration.\n"
"When this feature is enabled and a server returns a response that includes the header `Content-Encoding: gzip`, REST Client will automatically decode the content and proceed with the message handling."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "An example configuration could be:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "The REST Client falls back onto the Quarkus wide `quarkus.http.enable-compression` configuration property (which defaults to `false`) if no REST Client specific property is set."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "Proxy support"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "REST Client supports sending requests through a proxy. You can still rely on JVM proxy settings, but REST Client allows you to define a default proxy and any number of named proxy configurations that clients can reference."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "Proxy configuration is centralized in a Proxy Registry; configure proxies under the `quarkus.proxy` configuration root."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "Global proxy configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "You can define a default proxy configuration that will be used by all REST Clients that do not explicitly reference a named proxy configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "This configuration will cause all REST Clients, including `my-client`, to use the proxy at `localhost:8182` with the provided credentials."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "Named proxy configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "You can define named proxy configurations and have specific REST Clients use them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "`client1` is configured to use the `my-proxy` proxy configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "`client2` does not specify a proxy configuration name, so it will not use any proxy unless a default proxy configuration is defined."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "Using Credentials Provider"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid ""
"In addition to the `quarkus.proxy` settings, REST Client can obtain proxy credentials from the Quarkus Credentials Provider.\n"
"See link:https://quarkus.io/guides/credentials-provider[Credentials Provider] for more details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "Define a named proxy configuration `baby-proxy` without username and password."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "Configure the Credentials Provider to obtain the username and password for the proxy."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "The Credentials Provider is not used when `quarkus.proxy.password` (for global) or `quarkus.proxy.<named>.password` (for named) is not set."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "Local proxy for dev mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid ""
"When using the REST Client in dev mode, Quarkus has the ability to stand up a pass-through proxy which can be used as a target for Wireshark (or similar tools)\n"
"in order to capture all the traffic originating from the REST Client (this really makes sense when the REST Client is used against HTTPS services)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid ""
"To enable this feature, all that needs to be done is set the `enable-local-proxy` configuration option for the configKey corresponding to the client for which proxying is desired.\n"
"For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid ""
"When a REST Client does not use a config key (for example when it is created programmatically via `QuarkusRestClientBuilder`) then the class name can be used instead.\n"
"For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/rest-client.adoc
msgid "The port the proxy is listening can be found in startup logs. An example entry is:"
msgstr ""

